<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Doctor Appointment Scheduling App</title>
  <meta
    name="description"
    content="A professional project website for a Doctor Appointment Scheduling App."
  />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <header class="hero">
    <nav class="navbar container">
      <div class="logo">MediSchedule</div>
      <ul class="nav-links">
        <li><a href="#overview">Overview</a></li>
        <li><a href="#features">Features</a></li>
        <li><a href="#users">Users</a></li>
        <li><a href="#requirements">Requirements</a></li>
        <li><a href="#demo">Demo</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="hero-content container">
      <div class="hero-text">
        <p class="badge">Healthcare Scheduling Project</p>
        <h1>Doctor Appointment Scheduling App</h1>
        <p class="hero-description">
          A modern scheduling platform designed to help medical offices reduce
          booking errors, improve patient access, and streamline front desk
          operations.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-buttons">
          <a href="#features" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Features</a>
          <a href="#demo" class="btn btn-secondary">View Demo</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-card">
        <h3>Today's Appointments</h3>

        <div class="appointment-item">
          <div>
            <strong>9:00 AM</strong>
            <p>New Patient Visit</p>
          </div>
          <span class="status open">Confirmed</span>
        </div>

        <div class="appointment-item">
          <div>
            <strong>11:30 AM</strong>
            <p>Follow-Up Appointment</p>
          </div>
          <span class="status booked">Booked</span>
        </div>

        <div class="appointment-item">
          <div>
            <strong>2:15 PM</strong>
            <p>Annual Physical</p>
          </div>
          <span class="status reminder">Reminder Sent</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section id="overview" class="section container reveal">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        Many smaller medical offices still depend on phone calls, paper notes,
        or outdated systems to handle appointments. This project proposes a
        centralized appointment scheduling application that helps patients,
        doctors, and staff manage the scheduling process more efficiently.
      </p>

      <div class="stats-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>24</h3>
          <p>Week Project Plan</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>4</h3>
          <p>Main User Groups</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>6</h3>
          <p>Core Feature Areas</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>100%</h3>
          <p>Browser Accessible</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features" class="section alt-section">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          The platform is built around convenience, accuracy, and efficiency.
        </p>

        <div class="card-grid">
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Online Booking</h3>
            <p>Patients can choose a doctor, appointment type, date, and time.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Reschedule & Cancel</h3>
            <p>Appointments can be updated without forcing staff to start over.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Availability Tracking</h3>
            <p>Only open time slots are shown to prevent double booking.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Automated Reminders</h3>
            <p>Email or text reminders help lower the number of missed visits.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Reports</h3>
            <p>Staff can review daily schedules, no-shows, and office activity.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Secure Access</h3>
            <p>Role-based login protects patient and scheduling information.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="users" class="section container reveal">
      <h2>Users</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        The application supports several user types across the medical office.
      </p>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Patients</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Create accounts</li>
            <li>Book appointments</li>
            <li>View upcoming visits</li>
            <li>Cancel or reschedule</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Front Desk Staff</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Schedule appointments</li>
            <li>Manage daily calendar</li>
            <li>Update patient bookings</li>
            <li>Generate reports</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Doctors & Admins</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Review schedules</li>
            <li>Track appointment details</li>
            <li>Manage availability</li>
            <li>Monitor system use</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="requirements" class="section alt-section">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <h2>System Requirements</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          The system includes both functional and nonfunctional requirements.
        </p>

        <div class="requirements-layout">
          <div class="requirements-box">
            <h3>Functional Requirements</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>User login and account creation</li>
              <li>Search available appointment slots</li>
              <li>Schedule, cancel, and reschedule appointments</li>
              <li>Send automated reminders</li>
              <li>Generate scheduling reports</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="requirements-box">
            <h3>Nonfunctional Requirements</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Fast response time</li>
              <li>Mobile-friendly design</li>
              <li>Reliable data storage</li>
              <li>Secure access control</li>
              <li>Easy-to-use interface</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="demo" class="section container reveal">
      <h2>Appointment Demo</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        This sample form gives the site a more realistic project feel.
      </p>

      <div class="demo-grid">
        <form class="booking-form" id="bookingForm">
          <label for="patientName">Patient Name</label>
          <input type="text" id="patientName" placeholder="Enter patient name" required />

          <label for="doctor">Doctor</label>
          <select id="doctor" required>
            <option value="">Select doctor</option>
            <option>Dr. Martinez</option>
            <option>Dr. Kim</option>
            <option>Dr. Patel</option>
            <option>Dr. Chen</option>
          </select>

          <label for="date">Appointment Date</label>
          <input type="date" id="date" required />

          <label for="time">Appointment Time</label>
          <select id="time" required>
            <option value="">Select time</option>
            <option>9:00 AM</option>
            <option>10:30 AM</option>
            <option>1:15 PM</option>
            <option>3:00 PM</option>
          </select>

          <label for="type">Appointment Type</label>
          <select id="type" required>
            <option value="">Select type</option>
            <option>New Patient Visit</option>
            <option>Follow-Up</option>
            <option>Annual Physical</option>
            <option>Consultation</option>
          </select>

          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary full-btn">
            Book Appointment
          </button>
        </form>

        <div class="confirmation-box">
          <h3>Live Preview</h3>
          <p>
            Fill out the form to simulate an appointment booking for your project
            demo.
          </p>
          <div id="confirmationMessage" class="message-box">
            No appointment submitted yet.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container footer-content">
      <p>Doctor Appointment Scheduling App</p>
      <p>Created by Antony Benitez</p>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
